org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.blades

Interface SyncAgent<RESPONSE_TYPE>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Blade
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PrinterAgent, SyncAgentBase
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public interface SyncAgent<RESPONSE_TYPE>
extends Blade
    A SyncAgent is a blade with a StartSReq and which is dynamically added to a Reactor to interact with the blades of that Reactor. One of the advantages of a SyncAgent is to reduce the number of requests that pass between threads. The other can be to perform multiple local requests against the other blades in that targetReactor in isolation from other requests.

    Any needed parameters are not passed to the startSReq, but are instead are to be passed in the constructor of the subclasses of SyncAgent.
